From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PersonalTutor <personal-tutor@example.local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] build: include personal_tutor package in setuptools discovery

This is the *only* change PersonalTutor makes to an upstream DeepTutor
source tree. It adds `personal_tutor*` to the editable-install discovery
list and ships its bundled YAML/MD data, so that `pip install -e .` also
installs PersonalTutor and it becomes importable from any working
directory (not just the project root).

Why a patch (not a separate pyproject)?
---------------------------------------
The upstream capability registry imports `deeptutor.plugins.loader`
lazily, and that shim re-exports from `personal_tutor.plugins`. For the
shim to resolve, `personal_tutor` must be on `sys.path` regardless of the
current working directory — which requires it to be an installed package.
A single-line addition to the existing `[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
include` array plus its `package-data` entry is the minimal, idiomatic
way to achieve this; maintaining a second build file would fight the
single editable install the rest of the repo assumes.

Rebase notes
------------
On conflict, re-apply by ensuring `personal_tutor*` is present in the
`include` array under `[tool.setuptools.packages.find]` and that a
`personal_tutor = [...]` entry exists under `[tool.setuptools.package-data]`.
These two hunks are the entire surface of this patch.

Apply with:  git am patches/001-personal-tutor-package-include.patch
---
 pyproject.toml | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -208,7 +208,7 @@ version = {attr = "deeptutor.__version__.__version__"}
 
 [tool.setuptools.packages.find]
 where = ["."]
-include = ["deeptutor*", "deeptutor_cli*"]
+include = ["deeptutor*", "deeptutor_cli*", "personal_tutor*"]
 
 [tool.setuptools.package-data]
 # Runtime data shipped inside the deeptutor package: prompt YAMLs (loaded by
@@ -226,3 +226,5 @@ deeptutor = [
 deeptutor_cli = ["**/*.md"]
 deeptutor_web = ["**/*", ".next/**/*"]
+# PersonalTutor ships domain knowledge graphs as YAML and spec/README markdown;
+# importlib.resources.files() reads these at runtime so they must be packaged.
+personal_tutor = ["**/*.yaml", "**/*.yml", "**/*.md"]
-- 
